        "content": "<p>We now have automation for creating WASI 0.3.0 release rc's <span aria-label=\"tada\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f389\" role=\"img\" title=\"tada\">:tada:</span>  There's more to automate and there will certainly be more release candidates, but here's to getting started on stabilizing WASI P3 API's!!!</p>\n<p>The git tag in the wasi repos is <code>v0.3.0-rc-2025-08-15</code> as well as OCI artifacts tagged with <code>0.3.0-rc-2025-08-15</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Bash\"><pre><span></span><code>wkg<span class=\"w\"> </span>oci<span class=\"w\"> </span>pull<span class=\"w\"> </span>ghcr.io/webassembly/wasi/http:0.3.0-rc-2025-08-15\nwasm-tools<span class=\"w\"> </span>component<span class=\"w\"> </span>wit<span class=\"w\"> </span>webassembly_wasi_http.wasm<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>less\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Special thanks to <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"480579\">@Lann Martin</span> and <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"479055\">@Calvin Prewitt</span> for jumping on a <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasm-pkg-tools/issues/167\">wkg issue</a> that let this rollout happen today <span aria-label=\"heart\" class=\"emoji emoji-2764\" role=\"img\" title=\"heart\">:heart:</span> Also <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"344849\">@Yosh Wuyts</span> for being an awesome pair while working on the automation!</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasm-pkg-tools/issues/167\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasm-pkg-tools/issues/167\" title=\"Fails to decode 0.3 components · Issue #167 · bytecodealliance/wasm-pkg-tools\">Fails to decode 0.3 components · Issue #167 · bytecodealliance/wasm-pkg-tools</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Fails to parse 0.3 components. # build works wkg wit build -o \"wasi-clocks-0.3.0.wasm\" --wit-dir wit-0.3.0-draft # publish fails wkg oci push ghcr.io/webassembly/wasi/clocks-0.3.0:0.3.0-rc-2025-08-...</div></div></div>",
